  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Anticipatory Action on Water, Sanitation and Hygiene (WASH) to prevent and reduce human suffering, through provision of clean safe water and hygiene promotion services</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main objective of this project is to mitigate disease and malnutrition risks of the projected drought shock by ensuring supply of clean water and healthy practices in Sanaag, Togdheer, Mudug, Gedo and Lower Juba regions. The $2.25 million in CERF funding will enable IOM to rehabilitate 10 boreholes and drill 2 new boreholes that will benefit 52,000 people. In addition, IOM will rehabilitate or upgrade 13 motorized wells supporting 20,000 people and distribute 3,000 hygiene kits. In total, the project will support 72,000 people, including 14,400 women and 12,600 girls.</narrative>
  </description>
